@startuml Teacher_SetSchedule_Seq
title EduFlow LMS — Teacher: Set / Update Schedule Sequence

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceParticipant underline
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF

actor       Teacher        as T
participant "EduFlow UI"   as UI
participant "Schedule Service" as SS
participant "Database"     as DB
participant "Notification Service" as NS
actor       Student        as S

== Set New Schedule ==

T -> UI      : Open Schedule Manager
UI -> SS     : GET /schedules?teacherId={id}
SS -> DB     : SELECT existing schedules
DB --> SS    : schedules[]
SS --> UI    : Return schedules
UI --> T     : Display Schedule Dashboard

T -> UI      : Fill in schedule details\n(title, date, time, course)
UI -> SS     : POST /schedules { details }
SS -> DB     : INSERT schedule record
DB --> SS    : schedule_id
SS --> UI    : 201 Created { schedule_id }
UI --> T     : Confirm — "Schedule Created"

SS -> NS     : Trigger student notifications
NS -> S      : Email / Push: "New lesson scheduled"

== Update Existing Schedule ==

T -> UI      : Select existing schedule
UI -> SS     : GET /schedules/{schedule_id}
SS -> DB     : SELECT schedule by ID
DB --> SS    : schedule record
SS --> UI    : Return schedule details
UI --> T     : Display editable form

T -> UI      : Modify fields & submit
UI -> SS     : PUT /schedules/{schedule_id} { updated }
SS -> DB     : UPDATE schedule record
DB --> SS    : OK
SS --> UI    : 200 OK
UI --> T     : Confirm — "Schedule Updated"

SS -> NS     : Trigger update notifications
NS -> S      : Email / Push: "Schedule has been updated"

@enduml
